    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-12-18T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-12-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="152"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d152">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 893.51/701.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">British Ambassador</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">British Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-12-18">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 18, 1911</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Dear Mr. Knox</hi>: There seems to be some difference of
                    opinion among the representatives of the six powers at Peking regarding the <pb
                        facs="0223" n="107" xml:id="pg_107"/> desirability of making the loan
                    proposed to Yuan Shih Kai unless the revolutionaries agree, which it seems they
                    will not do, and my Government would like to know your view of the position
                    before a final decision is reached.</p>
                <p>Believe me [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">James Bryce</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
